  "original_title": "\u0db6\u0dd2\u0dad\u0dca\u0dad\u0dbb\u0dba\u0d9a \u0d8b\u0db4\u0dbb\u0dd2\u0db8 \u0dc3\u0dd2\u0dbd\u0dca\u0dbd\u0dbb \u0db8\u0dd2\u0dbd \u0db4\u0dc4\u0d9a\u0dd2\u0db1\u0dca \u0dc0\u0dd0\u0da9\u0dd2 \u0dc0\u0dd9\u0dba\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "The maximum retail price of an egg will increase by five",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "A senior officer of the Consumer Services Authority said that the Minister of Commerce has given permission to sell an egg for 50 rupees and as a result, measures have been taken to suspend the raids that found traders selling eggs at higher prices.",
        "Due to the Ministry of Commerce issuing a gazette notice fixing the maximum retail price of a white egg at 43 rupees and a red or brown egg at 45 rupees, the egg producers decided to increase the price of an egg to 50 rupees after considering the continuous requests that they could not sell eggs according to that gazette notice. A trade ministry official said that a fixed price will be fixed as soon as possible.",
        "Before the maximum retail price of an egg was fixed by a gazette notification, an egg was sold at a price between Rs 60 and Rs 70."
      ],
      "title_ents": [
        {
          "text": "five",
          "label": "CARDINAL"
        }
      ],
